- /data_hdd/ankermake-m5-protocol-django1982/web/service/pppp.py
- /data_hdd/ankermake-m5-protocol-django1982/web/lib/service.py

### Files to create
- internal/service/mqttqueue.go       — MqttQueue service (VERY HIGH complexity)
- internal/service/mqttqueue_test.go  — state machine + progress normalization tests
- internal/service/pppp.go            — PPPPService (LAN connection + xzyh dispatch)
- internal/service/pppp_test.go       — ConnectionReset restart test

### MqttQueue requirements (implement EXACTLY per Python)
- Embeds BaseWorker, implements Service interface (call BindHooks in constructor)
- WorkerRun: connects via internal/mqtt/client, subscribes to printer topics, dispatches on ct value
- ct=1000 state machine: 0=idle 1=printing 2=paused 8=aborted — emit Notify on every state change
- Progress: arrives as 0-10000 from MQTT, normalize to 0-100 (divide by 100)
- ct=1044: capture filename, call db.DB.RecordStart(filename) — deferred until next ct=1000 with status=1
- Print control commands: send via MQTT publish — 0=restart, 2=pause, 3=resume, 4=stop
- Forward relevant events to HomeAssistantService and TimelapseService via their Notify()
- On disconnect: return ServiceRestartSignal to trigger auto-restart

### PPPPService requirements
- Embeds BaseWorker, implements Service interface
- WorkerRun: use internal/pppp/client for LAN discovery + connect
- Dispatch incoming Xzyh frames to registered xzyh handlers (map[byte]func([]byte))
- On ConnectionReset or any pppp error: return ServiceRestartSignal
- Expose RegisterXzyhHandler(channel byte, fn func([]byte))

### Critical
- All goroutines respect context.Context
- No data races (will be tested with -race)
- WorkerRun must BLOCK (select on ctx.Done() or channel) — never busy-loop
- Use internal/db for history recording
- Package: github.com/django1982/ankerctl/internal/service

